to the editor lawrence white 's assertion that somehow ratings agencies should have known about enron credit and credibility op ed feb 24 overlooks three critical facts first ratings agencies rely on publicly available information along with information that issuers voluntarily provide us second we now know that enron withheld substantial material information from us and the marketplace in fact it went to great lengths to conceal information third we now know that the information enron did provide to us and to the marketplace was inaccurate unreliable and misleading we respectfully suggest that it would have been very difficult for anyone to see through the undisclosed data and misinformation john rutherfurd jr president and chief executive moody 's corporation new york feb 25 2002

